<%# HOVERING MEDITATION %>
  <div id="hovering_meditation" class="single__wrapper">
    <div class="single__content" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
      <a href="#hovering_meditation" class="guide__suggestion guide__suggestion__padding">
        <div class="guide__suggestion__number guide__suggestion__number--bottom">4.</div>
      </a>
      <h2 class="single__sub__header">Hovering Meditation</h2>
      <p>Having provided advice for NeverFap Deluxe for quite some time now, one of the things I've noticed is that a lot of people out there struggle to meditate via traditional means.</p>
      <p>In part due to poor mental health and in a lot of cases, due to what is commonly known as "brain fog" which can make it incredibly difficult to engage with our minds in any meaningful way.</p>
      <p>This is why I decided to create Hovering.</p>
      <p>I wanted to design a meditation technique which could help bridge the gap between traditional meditation, and simply choosing not to meditate at all, as is often the case for those who simply struggle to use their minds in any capacity.</p>
      <p>Ultimately Hovering has been designed to be easy to understand, simple to practice, as well as be accessible to people of all ages.</p>
      <p>If you would like to learn more about Hovering I highly encourage you to visit the <a class="link" href="/hovering">NeverFap Deluxe Hovering</a> section of this website which provides a basics overview of the practice.</p>

      <img style="width: 100%;" src="https://neverfapdeluxe.netlify.com/images/hovering_web.png"/>

      <p>Alternatively you can visit the <a class="link" href="https://tryhovering.com/">Hovering Website</a> which provides a much more comprehensive overview of Hovering.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="line__top"></div>
  <div class="line__bottom"></div>

  <%= partial "banners/hovering_banner.html", assigns %>

  <div class="line__top"></div>
  <div class="line__bottom"></div>
<%# HOVERING MEDITATION END %>


